6 R

Rmetametagen()MetaMeta

# 
library(meta)
## Loading required package: metadat
## Loading 'meta' package (version 8.0-1).
## Type 'help(meta)' for a brief overview.
library(ggplot2)

# 
study_data <- data.frame(
  study = paste("Study", 1:5),
  effect_size = c(0.5, 0.6, 0.2, 0.8, 0.4),
  se = c(0.1, 0.15, 0.2, 0.12, 0.18)
)

# Meta
meta_result <- metagen(TE = effect_size, seTE = se, studlab = study, data = study_data, common = TRUE, random = TRUE, method.tau = "DL")

# Meta
summary(meta_result)
##                           95%-CI %W(common) %W(random)

## Study 2 0.6000 [ 0.3060; 0.8940]       16.5       19.4

## Study 4 0.8000 [ 0.5648; 1.0352]       25.7       23.7
## Study 5 0.4000 [ 0.0472; 0.7528]       11.4       15.9
## 
## Number of studies: k = 5
## 
##                                       95%-CI    z  p-value
## Common effect model  0.5545 [0.4351; 0.6738] 9.11 < 0.0001

# Forest Plot
forest(meta_result, xlab = "Effect Size")

# Funnel Plot
funnel(meta_result, xlab = "Effect Size", ylab = "Standard Error")
